                0.105,
                0.187,
                0.872,
                0.253
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "Only one item needs a comment: the flow dividends on the cash account. The general principle for flows is to apply the Year 2 average rate for their translation into EUR. But there are some exceptions as for the dividends flow on the equity side which is translated at the Year 1 average rate."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.105,
                0.267,
                0.872,
                0.349
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "Considering the fact these dividends are valuated with such rate, then the payment must also be valuated with the same rate. That's the reason why we extract a flow dividends for (400) from the net variation of cash for (1200). The remaining (800) is supposed to represent cash operations with the outside world and valuated at Year 2 average rate."
        },
        {
            "type": "text",
            "bbox": [
                0.106,
                0.364,
                0.518,
                0.38
            ],
            "angle": 0,
            "content": "The main principles for the translation are"
